# 🔄 Integrating the Story Graph with the SDK & CI/CD Pipeline

This guide details how to bridge the **NLP Story Graph Engine** with the **AethelFrame SDK** and **GitHub Actions CI/CD**. It covers data flow, schema mapping, orchestration scripts, pipeline adjustments, and runtime pacing alignment.

---

## 🧩 1. Data Flow Architecture

```mermaid
graph LR
  A[Raw Sources\nURLs/Text/Archives] --> B(Story Graph Engine)
  B --> C[Structured Graph JSON\nNodes/Edges/Acts/Accuracy]
  C --> D[SDK Payload Builder]
  D --> E[CI/CD Dispatcher]
  E --> F[AethelFrame API\nScript → Avatar → Voice → Render]
  C -.-> G[Pacing & B-Roll Composer\nScene markers, IK triggers]
```

The Story Graph acts as a **deterministic pre-processor**. Its output replaces freeform prompt engineering with structured, causally-linked narrative directives that the SDK passes directly to `generate_script` and `compose_scene`.

