## 🎭 6. Runtime Pacing & Scene Alignment

The Story Graph's temporal nodes directly drive audio-visual synchronization:

| Graph Component | Rendering Engine Action |
|-----------------|-------------------------|
| **`pacing_beats[].duration_pct`** | TTS prosody engine allocates syllables proportionally. High-weight beats receive breath pauses and pitch drift. |
| **`broll_markers[].time_offset_sec`** | Scene composer crossfades HDRI/archival B-roll at exact frame boundaries. Prevents "talking head" fatigue. |
| **`ik_triggers[].node_id`** | Inverse Kinematics rig loads preset (`head_lower_pause`, `hand_gesture_sweep`) synced to audio RMS spikes. |
| **`nodes[].accuracy`** | LLM script generator appends UI tags (`[Verified]` = neutral delivery, `[Speculative]` = softer cadence + subtitle disclaimer). |

**Pro Tip:** Use the `story_graph_weights` object to bias generation:
- `causality_priority: 0.9` → Strict chronological/causal chaining (academic docs)
- `emotional_arc_weight: 0.8` → Thematic/emphasis-driven pacing (narrative/mythic)
- `historical_precision: 0.4` → Creative liberties allowed (fictional/artistic)

